            Home > Grecourt                      Gate > News Stories > 2008-09                      News              Date:                  2/23/10                                 April                    Hoxie Foley ’69 to Speak February 25 Thursday, February 25, 4:30 p.m. in Seelye 106. Lecture                    by April Hoxie Foley '69, who served as U.S. Ambassador to                    the Republic of Hungary from 2006 to 2009, and in 2009 received                    the Hungarian military's highest civilian honor. Previously                    Ambassador Foley worked for Pfizer, Reader's Digest, and                    PepsiCo before serving as first vice-president and vice chairman                    of the Export-Import Bank of the United States.                 










 













